1. Using the echo command print in console "Hello World". Here is some info about echo command [https://discuss.codecademy.com/t/what-are-practical-uses-of-the-echo-command/394788]

"echo "hello world" > lab-bash"

(base) marina@MacBook-MacBook-Pro-de-Marina morning % cd lab-bash
(base) marina@MacBook-MacBook-Pro-de-Marina lab-bash % ls
Lab Bash	inputs		lorem-copy	readme.md
exercices	lorem		outputs
(base) marina@MacBook-MacBook-Pro-de-Marina lab-bash % echo "hello world" > lab-bash
(base) marina@MacBook-MacBook-Pro-de-Marina lab-bash % ls
exercices	lab-bash	lorem-copy	readme.md
inputs		lorem		outputs
(base) marina@MacBook-MacBook-Pro-de-Marina lab-bash % 

2. Create a new directory called new_dir.

"mkdir new_dir"

